TITLE: Sailors say aircraft carrier that had multiple suicides occur among crew was uninhabitable
SUMMARY: The commanding officer stood before the sailors of the USS George Washington's security team. One of their own, Xavier Sandor, had taken his life a few weeks earlier in mid-April, and the captain had come down to speak with the 110 or so young men and women who worked closely with him.

TITLE: Abortion rights activists in the US can learn from recent progress on abortion access in Latin America
SUMMARY: The prospect of the United States overturning decades of abortion rights, which materialized this week in a leaked draft opinion by Supreme Court Justice Samuel Alito, triggered shock waves in many countries in Latin America, where many feminist organizations have often looked at the US as a model of greater reproductive rights and freedoms.

TITLE: Thomas says government institutions shouldn't be 'bullied' following leak of draft opinion on abortion
SUMMARY: Justice Clarence Thomas, following the leak of a draft majority opinion overturning Roe v. Wade, said Friday that government institutions shouldn't be "bullied" into delivering what some see as the preferred outcome.

TITLE: Hot Wheels launches first remote-controlled wheelchair toy in partnership with Paralympian
SUMMARY: Hot Wheels is expanding representation for kids who use wheelchairs -- with the company's first-ever remote-controlled wheelchair toy.

TITLE: Colin Firth and Toni Colette add drama to a true crime case in 'The Staircase'
SUMMARY: This week, check out Colin Firth and Toni Collette in true crime drama "The Staircase," follow the story of a real-life attorney and one of the biggest Social Security fraud cases in history in "The Big Conn," and get pumped up for "Star Trek: Strange New Worlds."

TITLE: To save itself, Netflix might have to play nice with an industry it battled for years
SUMMARY: Netflix is still reeling from its stock plunge last month after losing subscribers for the first time in more than a decade.

TITLE: GOP still favored in midterms, despite possible overturning of Roe v. Wade
SUMMARY: The recent leak of a draft US Supreme Court opinion that would overturn Roe v. Wade seemed to give Democrats a winning issue to rally base and swing voters in the midterm elections. But our new CNN poll shows that such hopes are likely unfounded, Harry Enten writes.

TITLE: These young Black influencers eat, sleep and shoot videos at a mansion near Atlanta. Together they have 30 million followers
SUMMARY: Ten young African Americans left school and full-time jobs to move into a suburban Atlanta mansion called the Collab Crib, where they create viral videos for TikTok and Instagram. Now many are earning more money than their parents.

TITLE: How to survive an alligator attack -- or better yet, avoid one entirely
SUMMARY: There are millions of alligators in the US South but very few attacks. Here's how to fend off an alligator attack if you're the rare person in a fight for your life.

TITLE: Russia's war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Evacuation efforts are continuing at the Azovstal steel plant in Mariupol after Russian forces breached the perimeter this week, according to a Ukrainian commander inside.  Follow here for live updates.

TITLE: Roe v. Wade reversal would put local prosecutors on the front lines of the abortion fight
SUMMARY: The state-by-state patchwork of abortion restrictions that a reversal of Roe v. Wade would render will be even more complicated by the approaches of local prosecutors and law enforcement officials charged with enforcing abortion bans.

TITLE: How Elon Musk could impact Twitter's battles over speech abroad
SUMMARY: Since Elon Musk announced he was buying Twitter last month, the billionaire has sent out tweet after tweet outlining his plans for the platform, touching on everything from new features to security updates to monetization. But Musk's overarching reason for committing billions of dollars to buy Twitter is to ensure the platform bolsters free speech.

TITLE: North Korea fires ballistic missile into Sea of Japan
SUMMARY: A short-range ballistic missile fired by North Korea Saturday reached an altitude of about 37 miles (60 kilometers) over its 373-mile (600km) trajectory, according to South Korea's Joint Chiefs of Staff.

TITLE: Antarctica's majestic underwater world is trying to adapt to a warmer planet
SUMMARY: Icebergs surrounded a team of researchers in January as they cruised toward Antarctica. The team had been studying a thriving underwater ecosystem near the continent for years, but thanks to new modeling and powerful instrumentation they were able to navigate through a crumbling landscape of ice to their destination.

TITLE: Heroic masked Embiid returns to lift 76ers to crucial Game 3 win as Mavericks finally end Suns jinx
SUMMARY: Donning a protective face mask, Joel Embiid looked and acted the role of superhero on Friday night.

TITLE: 2022 Kentucky Derby: Everything you need to know about the 'Greatest Two Minutes in Sports'
SUMMARY: The 148th edition of the Kentucky Derby is set to take place on Saturday as the iconic race looks to move on from last year's controversy.

TITLE: Record-breaking Mali nonuplets celebrate their first birthday
SUMMARY: The world-famous nonuplets born to a couple from Mali, West Africa have celebrated their first birthday with a small party at home.

TITLE: Mother's Day isn't a celebration for everyone
SUMMARY: You may be grieving the loss of a parent or a parent who didn't treat you right. Here's what some people have done to navigate a painful time.

TITLE: Crawley Town FC manager John Yems out after allegations he used discriminatory language
SUMMARY: Crawley Town FC manager John Yems is no longer with the club following allegations of using discriminatory language and behavior toward players, the League Two club announced on Friday.

TITLE: Wait, Trader Joe was a real guy?
SUMMARY: Turns out Trader Joe was a real guy, and his shrewd instincts led him to create a counter-culture grocery empire.

TITLE: Travel news: Glass bridges, space hotels and a beautiful reunion after 23 years
SUMMARY: In this week's travel news roundup, CNN Travel looks at space hotels through the ages, Sicily's new "Little America" and a new glass-bottomed bridge in Vietnam.

TITLE: Michelin menus in turmoil as France faces foie gras crisis
SUMMARY: France's love for foie gras goose paté has endured controversy over animal cruelty, but appetites are now being hit by an invisible threat to its treasured delicacy.

TITLE: The two largest reservoirs in California are already at 'critically low levels' and the dry season is just starting
SUMMARY: According to the latest report from the US Drought Monitor, two of the state's largest reservoirs — Shasta Lake and Lake Oroville — are at "critically low levels."

TITLE: Why manhunts like the one for Vicky White and Casey White fascinate us
SUMMARY: The disappearance of Alabama corrections officer Vicky White and convict Casey White has grabbed the public's attention -- and a few factors play a part.

TITLE: Reward offered for information after 2 dolphins died in Texas and Florida following interactions with humans
SUMMARY: Officials are offering rewards for information on people who may have harmed two dolphins that later died in Texas and Florida.

TITLE: A river otter was spotted in the Detroit River for the first time in 100 years
SUMMARY: A river otter has been spotted in the Detroit River for the first time in a century.

TITLE: Sri Lanka president declares new state of emergency as protests roil island
SUMMARY: Sri Lanka's President Gotabaya Rajapaksa declared a state of emergency on Friday, after prolonged protests and a general strike shuttered schools, businesses, and transport services.

TITLE: US woman tracks down rightful owners of long-lost photo album in war-torn Ukrainian city
SUMMARY: An American woman who bought an old photo album online was determined to find its rightful owners in Ukraine and return it.

TITLE: Customs seized over $10 million worth of counterfeit Rolex watches
SUMMARY: US Customs and Border Protection officers in Indianapolis seized two shipments of counterfeit Rolex watches on April 27 and 29. The fake luxury watches would have had a total value of $10.1 million if real, according to CBP.

TITLE: Austrian climber found dead on the slopes of North America's tallest peak
SUMMARY: The body of an Austrian climber who was last heard from a week ago has been found on the slopes of Alaska's Mount Denali, authorities said on Friday.
